{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"165397e1-785c-4b52-b72d-62fcd39f0c9f","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: verify details\n}\n```\n\n**Why switch:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`)\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you inspect the exception","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b8f68805-4d97-45f7-bcb2-1af926e187b5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question - no need to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":240,"requestId":"082C:CC8AF:C5EC6E:E6C848:69EAC5E9"},"id":"57759d29-6ea7-4b64-b44c-726d5c216a8b","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:22:54.992Z","parentId":"a7384d0d-06b6-4324-906d-3f45da6632d8"}
